revision.text:
void '''SoundSequenceOnSector''' (int tag, string seqname, int location);
== Usage ==
Plays a sound sequence defined in [[SNDSEQ]] lump. The ''location'' parameter determines from where exactly the sound comes. Possible values are the following constants: *'''SECSEQ_FLOOR''': From the floor and below *'''SECSEQ_CEILING''': From the ceiling and up *'''SECSEQ_FULLHEIGHT''': At any height from the sector *'''SECSEQ_INTERIOR''': Between the floor and ceiling
